## English (English)

This license governs the use of the "Merely" software (hereinafter — "the Software") and establishes rights and restrictions for users. The Author of the Software is Yevhenii Nazarov, available at https://github.com/AriTeilWork.

### 1. Permissions:
1.1. Free use of the Software for personal and educational purposes is permitted.  
1.2. Studying, modifying, and creating derivative projects based on the Software is permitted, provided they are made available to other users (open access), except for derivative projects created by the Author (Yevhenii Nazarov), which may be proprietary.

### 2. Prohibitions:
2.1. Selling, distributing, or using the Software for commercial purposes without the written permission of the Author is prohibited.  
2.2. Claiming authorship of the original Software is prohibited.

### 3. Copyright and Author's Rights:
3.1. The Author (Yevhenii Nazarov) retains the exclusive right to use the Software for commercial purposes, including the creation of proprietary derivative projects, without any restrictions imposed by this license.  
3.2. The Author has the sole discretion to grant or deny permission for commercial use of the Software to third parties.

### 4. Disclaimer of Warranty:
The Software is provided "as is" without any express or implied warranties, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose. The user assumes all risks associated with the use of the Software. The Author (Yevhenii Nazarov) shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages, including loss of profits, arising from the use or inability to use the Software, even if the Author has been advised of the possibility of such damages.

### Governing Law:
This license is governed by the rules of private international law (conflict of laws). Any disputes arising under this license shall be resolved in accordance with the applicable law determined based on international conflict of laws principles.

